OL,6,FBut he added: "This matter was only
OL,7,Fone of several matters dealt with in a
OL,8,Ffast-paced and wide-ranging interview.
OL,10,F"She had made clear in her exchanges
OL,11,Fthat she did not believe that the
OL,12,Finformation provided by the Member for
OL,13,FGower was sufficient for her to take
OL,14,Faction, given her position as a
OL,15,FMinister.
OL,17,F"This view was endorsed by the
OL,18,Fofficial advice which she received
OL,19,Fonce a formal approach was made by the
OL,20,FMP for Gower."
